## License Addendum for agon-bbc-basic-adl-ez80asm

ALL TERMS OF THE ORIGINAL LICENSE AND COPYRIGHT CLAIMS APPLY. THIS ADDENDUM DOES NOT ALTER, EXTEND, MAKE NEW CLAIMS, OR OTHERWISE MODIFY THE ORIGINAL CLAIMS AND TERMS CONTAINED HERIN.

This is a derivative work of the original BBC BASIC for Z80 created by R.T. Russell, and further modified by Dean Belfield for use on the Agon Light family of retrocomputers. The code in this repository further modifies the source to be compatible with the Agon's native assembler, agon-ez80asm by Jeroen Venema. (See README.md for further details.)

#### Disclaimer
All modifications in this repository, including those necessary for `ez80asm` compatibility are provided "as-is" with no implied warranty, in alignment with the terms of the original license.

#### Author Information
This fork of BBC BASIC for Z80 is maintained by Brandon R. Gates (Discord: BeeGee747). The full source code for this fork is available at https://github.com/bgates747/agon-bbc-basic-adl-ez80asm